<subSubSection id="AFD5650EFFE6833E37BCC1B8FA69F809" pageId="6" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E7703685FFE6833E37BCC1B8FA69F809" blockId="6.[151,1436,1863,2006]" pageId="6" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE6833E37BCC1B8FECDF873" bold="true" box="[197,317,1941,1967]" pageId="6" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="20CF4D06FFE6833E3635C1B8FDCEF872" box="[332,574,1941,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minitaurella">
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE6833E3635C1B8FDCEF872" box="[332,574,1941,1966]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="22">Perittia minitaurella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a unicolorous mottled grey species, externally similar to 
<taxonomicName id="20CF4D06FFE6833E3387C1B8FED9F80A" authority="Staudinger" authorityName="Staudinger" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piperatella">
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE6833E3387C1B8FA6CF872" box="[1278,1436,1941,1966]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="22">P. piperatella</emphasis>
(Staudinger)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE6833E361AC191FE39F809" box="[355,457,1980,2005]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="22">P. r a v i d a</emphasis>
, which are paler and smaller. Both of these species have longer labial palpi than 
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE6833E32FFC191FA69F809" box="[1414,1433,1980,2005]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="22">P.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AFD5650EFFE7833F37EEC6B5FB53FE45" pageId="7" pageNumber="23" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="E7703685FFE7833F37EEC6B5FB53FE45" blockId="7.[151,1436,152,410]" pageId="7" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="20CF4D06FFE7833F37EEC6B5FED7FF6D" box="[151,295,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minitaurella">
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE7833F37EEC6B5FED7FF6D" box="[151,295,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="23">minitaurella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Unlike 
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE7833F36F7C6B5FE05FF6D" box="[398,501,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="23">P. r a v i d a</emphasis>
, the flagellum of antenna is distinctly serrate in 
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE7833F334FC6B5FB1BFF6D" box="[1078,1259,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="20CF4D06FFE7833F334FC6B5FB17FF6D" box="[1078,1255,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minitaurella">P. minitaurella</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="20CF4D06FFE7833F37C1C692FEAAFF04" box="[184,346,191,216]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piperatella">
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE7833F37C1C692FEAAFF04" box="[184,346,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="23">P. piperatella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinctive as the termen of the valva is only weakly emarginated (see 
<bibRefCitation id="835E4B74FFE7833F339FC693FF14FF23" author="Traugott-Olsen" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" refString="Traugott-Olsen, E. (1995 a) Phylogeny of the subfamily Elachistinae s. str. Part I: Mendesiini, with some taxonomic revision and descriptions of new taxa (Lepidoptera, Elachistidae). SHILAP Revista de lepidopterologica, 23, 153 - 180." type="journal article" year="1995" yearSuffix="a">
Traugott-Olsen 
<number id="510724A2FFE7833F37EEC6C8FF26FF23" box="[151,214,229,255]" pageId="7" pageNumber="23" value="1995.0">1995</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
). Male genitalia are close to 
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE7833F3542C6C8FD52FF22" box="[571,674,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="23">P. r a v i d a</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="20CF4D06FFE7833F3598C6C8FBD0FF23" authority="Walsingham" authorityName="Walsingham" box="[737,1056,229,255]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carlinella">
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE7833F3598C6C8FC81FF22" box="[737,881,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="23">P. carlinella</emphasis>
(Walsingham)
</taxonomicName>
(illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation id="835E4B74FFE7833F33B6C6C8FF27FEFA" author="Kaila" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" refString="Kaila, L. &amp; Karsholt, O. (2002) Contribution to the Lepidoptera fauna of the Madeira island Part 3. Elachistidae. Beitrage zur Entomologie, 52, 225 - 233." type="journal article" year="2002">
Kaila &amp; Karsholt 
<number id="510724A2FFE7833F37EEC721FF27FEFA" box="[151,215,268,294]" pageId="7" pageNumber="23" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), from which they differ as follows: the valva is longer and narrower in 
<taxonomicName id="20CF4D06FFE7833F333BC721FB26FEF9" box="[1090,1238,268,293]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carlinella">
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE7833F333BC721FB26FEF9" box="[1090,1238,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="23">P. carlinella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than in either 
<taxonomicName id="20CF4D06FFE7833F32FFC721FED7FE97" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minitaurella">
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE7833F32FFC721FED7FE97" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="23">P. minitaurella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE7833F3637C71FFE44FE97" box="[334,436,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="23">P. r a v i d a</emphasis>
; sacculus of the valva is weakly tapered in 
<taxonomicName id="20CF4D06FFE7833F34CFC71FFBB5FE97" box="[950,1093,306,331]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carlinella">
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE7833F34CFC71FFBB5FE97" box="[950,1093,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="23">P. carlinella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
unlike that in 
<taxonomicName id="20CF4D06FFE7833F3396C71FFA6CFE97" box="[1263,1436,306,331]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minitaurella">
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE7833F3396C71FFA6CFE97" box="[1263,1436,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="23">P. minitaurella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE7833F37B1C774FEDDFEAE" box="[200,301,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="23">P. r a v i d a</emphasis>
. The male genitalia of 
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE7833F3544C774FD15FEAE" box="[573,741,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="23">P. m i n i t a u re l l a</emphasis>
are similar to those of 
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE7833F348DC774FB90FEAE" box="[1012,1120,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="23">P. r a v i d a,</emphasis>
but the sacculus is distally more bent and tapered to a less pointed apex in 
<taxonomicName id="20CF4D06FFE7833F35BCC7ADFC81FE45" box="[709,881,384,409]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minitaurella">
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE7833F35BCC7ADFC81FE45" box="[709,881,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="23">P. minitaurella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as compared to 
<emphasis id="D5BBEA97FFE7833F334BC7ADFB53FE45" box="[1074,1187,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="20CF4D06FFE7833F334BC7ADFB6EFE45" box="[1074,1182,384,409]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ravida">P. ravida</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
